
# Data Pre-processing

Data preprocessing is an essential stage in the machine learning pipeline that improves data quality before model training.

The preprocessing workflow includes:

## Handling Missing Values

- Checked the dataset for null values.
- Numerical values are replaced using the median if required.
- Categorical values are replaced using the mode.
- The dataset used in this project contained no missing values.

## Handling Outliers

- Outliers were detected using the Interquartile Range (IQR) method.
- Extreme rainfall values were capped using lower and upper IQR boundaries.
- This reduces the impact of abnormal observations while preserving the dataset.

## Handling Categorical Values

- Checked the dataset for categorical features.
- Label Encoding is applied when categorical values are present.
- The current dataset contains only numerical attributes, so no encoding was required.

## Splitting the Dataset

The dataset is divided into:

- Training Set: 80%
- Testing Set: 20%

A stratified split is used to maintain the original flood and non-flood class distribution.

## Feature Scaling

Feature scaling is performed using StandardScaler.

The scaler:

- Learns the statistical properties from the training data.
- Applies the same transformation to testing data.
- Prevents data leakage.
- Improves model performance, especially for KNN.
